					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">- The PPU address bit rising/falling thing seems too complex. Most emulators were using CRCs to identify a certain ROM and a "best" IRQ method of counting, using PPU scanlines as reference. An hack to fix some titles such as MegaManIII was to check the sprite pattern bank 0000h or 1000h.
<br />
<br />- Is there an alternate method for proper MMC3 emulation, or near enough? My PPU code renders using tilecaching + pixel-by-pixel, without pre-caching tiles like the NES does. Well, that's it.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><strong>Zepper</strong><br /><a href="http://rocknes.web.fc2.com/" class="postlink"><em>RockNES developer</em></a></div>
