					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">hap wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Monitoring all writes to the PPU Address to see if any change the IRQ counter is only useful if you're trying to pass blarrg's tests. I don't think any game actually relies on this.</div><br />Knowing that literary hundreds of games use the MMC3, you'd want emulation to be very accurate.</div>
<br />Would you rather have <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha"><li>accurate at 50 percent speed on a handheld device, </li><li>hacky at 100 percent speed on a handheld device, or </li><li>accurate at 50 percent speed on a large, expensive laptop? </li></ol> Accurate, fast, small: choose two. That's the breaks when your target platform has only 280,896 CPU cycles to emulate 29,780.5 NES CPU cycles.</div>

